Popular entertainment entrepreneur, Alex Ozone kick started the new year in a philanthropic fashion by donating to the underprivileged in the society. Ozone recently visited a charity home which caters for the abandoned, abused, orphaned, and homeless children, The Lions Village Motherless Babies situated at Lekki, Lagos State and the atmosphere was lifted as the promoter in the company of popular musician, Gabriel Amanyi, widely known as Terry G, and friends as they staged a grand entrance to the children’s home. The showbiz promoter celebrated with the children and parted with lots of goodies, food items, academic materials and an undisclosed amount of money for the welfare of the children. Abiodun meets UK companies in investment drive NASS N128bn budget: Senators feign ignorance We have identified ‘many enemies’ of Oko Oloyun —Lagos… Lagos govt to meet with NNPC on compensation for Abule Egba… Speaking at the event, the Anambra-born businessman who was in obvious elated mood disclosed that: “Taking care of the needy is God’s will, especially children. I’m frantically happy and fulfilled with joy seeing the children basking and rejoicing in the spirit of love.” To demonstrate that the visit was not a one-off event, he promised the home to return the following month. “I will be back mid-next month with more merriment and music to celebrate the month of love these beautiful children”, he stated. Meanwhile, Ozone’s friend and artiste under his 03Media management outfit, Terry G, thrilled the children with songs and dance which will linger in the memory of the children as the visitors made the atmosphere a colourful one for the charity home members. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OW